  "prompt": "Why does Draco Malfoy not have good relations with Harry Potter?",
  "response": "Draco Malfoy and Harry Potter have strained relations for several reasons throughout the \"Harry Potter\" series:\n\n1. **Conflict in Values**: Draco embodies many of the values and prejudices associated with pureblood supremacy, which is contrary to Harry's more inclusive and egalitarian beliefs.\n\n2. **Rivalry from the Start**: Their poor relationship starts early, with Draco attempting to befriend Harry when he first arrives at Hogwarts. Harry declines his offer, opting to be friends with Ron Weasley, who Draco considers to be beneath him.\n\n3. **House Rivalry**: Draco is sorted into Slytherin, while Harry is sorted into Gryffindor. The long-standing rivalry between these two houses fuels their animosity.\n\n4. **Different Alliances**: Throughout the series, Draco becomes increasingly involved with the followers of Voldemort (Death Eaters), while Harry\u2019s mission is to fight against them.\n\n5. **Personal Enmity**: Draco often goes out of his way to antagonize Harry and his friends. Harry\u2019s reactions to Draco\u2019s provocations contribute to their mutual dislike.\n\nOverall, their negative relationship is built on a mixture of personal slights, differing beliefs, and their respective social circles and allegiances.",
